What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

> Expected unique values in the array1, for one seed (default) it works, but when seed=22 it does not obey. 
```log
Randomized values in array1: '{'hd2, 'hff, 'hff, 'hea, 'h24, 'h9a, 'h94, 'h38, 'hc5, 'h5b}
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
```sh
	verilator --binary -Wno-lint -Wno-CONSTRAINTIGN test15.sv
	./obj_dir/Vtest15
	./obj_dir/Vtest15 +verilator+seed+22
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?
> Verilator 5.043 devel rev v5.026-1852-gaff501f5c

What OS and distribution are you using?

> WSL, Ubunutu

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
> Not sure 

Test:
```systemverilog
class UniqueMultipleOf3Array;
  rand bit [7:0] array1[10];

  // Constraint to ensure the elements in the array are unique
  constraint unique_c {
    unique {array1};  // Ensure unique values in the array
  }

  // --------------------------------------------------
  // Explicit uniqueness checker (post-solve validation)
  // --------------------------------------------------
  function bit check_unique();
    for (int i = 0; i < $size(array1); i++) begin
      for (int j = i + 1; j < $size(array1); j++) begin
        if (array1[i] == array1[j]) begin
          $error("UNIQUENESS VIOLATION: array1[%0d] == array1[%0d] == 0x%h", i, j, array1[i]);
          return 0;
        end
      end
    end
    return 1;
  endfunction

  function void post_randomize();
    $display("Randomized values in array1: %p", array1);

    if (!check_unique()) begin
      $fatal(1, "Post-randomize uniqueness check FAILED");
    end
    foreach (array1[i]) begin
      $display("array1[%0d] = %0d", i, array1[i]);
    end
  endfunction

endclass : UniqueMultipleOf3Array

module test;
  initial begin
    // Create an instance of the UniqueMultipleOf3Array class
    UniqueMultipleOf3Array array_instance = new();

    // Attempt to randomize and verify the constraints
    assert (array_instance.randomize())
    else $error("Randomization failed!");
  end
endmodule

```

